MS. Copt. d. 14(1-5) (P)

Trismegistos no.: 107826

Summary Catalogue no.: 34646-34650

Pauline Epistles

Contents

New Testament, Pauline Epistles, 1 including Corinthians 5-8 , 2 Corinthians 3-4, Hebrews 6-7, 9-10.1, Philippians 1-2, Col. 1-2

Language(s): Coptic (Sahidic dialect)

Physical Description

Form: codex
Support: parchment
Extent: 1 page and 8 pages. The dimensions given are for the full page.
Dimensions (leaf): 184 × 152 mm.

Layout

2 columns.

Hand(s)

Written in square uncials of an early type and at the end of lines certain letters are wriiten smaller than the rest, and in many ways it resemles closely the Codex Sinaiticus. On the other hand there are several features which seem to point to a later date, probably the early 5th century.

History

Origin: 400-450 ; Egypt (Ancient)

Provenance and Acquisition

Found in Apa Apollo Monasterion (Deir el-Bala’izah)

Given by Prof. W. Flinders Petrie, 1908

Record Sources

Summary description abbreviated by Blane Aitchison from the following sources:
P. Kahle, Balaizah: Coptic Texts from Deir el-Bala'izah in Upper Egypt, 2 vols. (London, 1954), Vol. 1, 350-366
Trismegistos: an interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphical resources

Availability

This item may only be consulted by prior arrangement with a curator. To make an application, please click the request button above. When your request is received, you will be asked to contact the relevant person.

MS. Copt. d. 45 (P)

Trismegistos no.: 77970

Summary Catalogue no.: 34792

Contents

Greek tax - account Abrechnung, Steuern

Language(s): Greek

Physical Description

Form: sheet
Support: papyrus
Dimensions (leaf): 267 × 146 mm.

Layout

3 columns. The first contains the amount paid by each person for poll tax, the second is for the 'expenses for twelve months', and the third is the amount for 'those who are away from home'.

Hand(s)

Miniscule script.

History

Origin: 675-799 ; Apa Apollo Monasterion (Deir el-Bala’izah)

Support: parchment
Extent: 2 fragments.

Layout

Columns and lines ruled.

Hand(s)

Written in square uncials of the 5th or 6th century. The manuscript is difficult to read and the supralineal strokes are almost illegible.

History

Provenance and Acquisition

Given by Prof. W. Flinders Petrie, 1908

Physical Description

Two pages from a martyrdom of a number of soldiers before Arianos.

Contents

martyrdom

Language(s): Coptic (Sahidic dialect)

Physical Description

Form: codex
Support: parchment
Extent: Two pages forming a single leaf. Both pages have the same dimensions.
Dimensions (leaf): 95 × 44 mm.

Layout

1 column.

Hand(s)

Written in small square uncials of the 6th or 7th centuries.

History

Origin: 500-699 ; Egypt (Ancient)

Provenance and Acquisition
